{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Backpay the \u00a320 covid uplift to people on Legacy Benefits",
        "additional_details": "I feel that the disabled and people on Legacy Benefits, were discriminated against by the Government when they made their decision to only pay people on Universal Credit, when they were getting pretty much the same amount of benefits before the uplift, and people with disabilities have a difficult time to begin with but during the pandemic they struggled much more than the people on Universal Credit, and had just as many expenses if not more, than the average person.",
        "background": "The government paid everyone on universal credit \u00a320 per week from April 20 to October 21 but not to the disabled on Legacy Benefits. We all struggled the same and a lot of disabled people even more than others during the pandemic so I want it paid to them backdated.",
